<br>
Working for a firm of financial advisers we've watched as share prices droped to 1/100th of their original value, profits sink, and dividends drop. As a result people are being laid off. People don't want to invest new money.<br>
<br>
There is a rule that says when manufacturing output falls for 3 months running we're actually in recession and as of December 1st we're actually in the first ever global recession, and the slowdown has been enormous.<br>
<br>
Yes what happened that day is the major contributor but it has not been unusual for CEOs of the big companies issuinig directives to cut 5% of jobs worldwide and it looks like Saav got on the tail of this one. I'm willing to bet the same CEOs also took a payrise on January 1st as they always do and probably a healthy christmas bonus. It plain and simple sucks.<br>
<br>
Saav, have a little faith. Nobody who truly wants to work stays unemployed for long. <p><CENTER><A HREF="http://ak.lonelygamer.com">
